$ Oracle: Towards an autonomous database


During its → development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions[releases], Oracle had a focus on automation of → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration[administration tasks].
An automated database is easier to be put into the cloud.

9i:
  • Automatic Query Rewrite 
  • Automatic Undo Management 

10g:
  • Automatic → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/memory-management[Memory Management]
  • Automatic Segment Space Mgmt 
  • Automatic → development/databases/Oracle/optimizer/statistics/gathering[Statistics Gathering]
  • Automatic Storage Management 
  • Automatic Workload Repository 
  • Automatic Diagnostic Monitor 

11g:
  • Automatic SQL Tuning 
  • Automatic Workload Capture / Replay 
  • Automatic → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement/execution/plan/management[SQL Plan Management]
  • Automatic Capture of SQL Monitor 
  • Automatic Data Optimization 

→ development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/12c:
  • Autonomous Health Framework 
  • Automatic Diagnostic Framework 
  • Automatic Refresh of Clones 

→ development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/18c:
  • Automatic Columnar Flash 
  • Automatic IM population 
  • Automatic Application Continuity

→ development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/19c:
  • Automatic Indexes, Partitions 
  • Automatic Materialized views

